    "answer": "Monitor performance via DMVs: 1) Query `sys.dm_exec_requests` to check active requests and their status. 2) Use `sys.dm_pdw_exec_requests` to see distributed execution state. 3) Look for wait type `BACKEND_STARTUP` or `COMPUTE_NODE_ALLOCATION` in `sys.dm_pdw_waits`. 4) If `wait_time` is high and query execution starts only after 10-30 seconds, it indicates the capacity was paused or idle, and Polaris is cold-starting compute nodes. 5) Track `sys.dm_pdw_request_steps` to pinpoint which query step was delayed by node allocation.",
