    "answer": "The `PREDICT` function enables native scoring: 1) The user registers an ONNX model in the database. 2) T-SQL compile phase: the query parser flags the `PREDICT` function call. 3) During execution, the SQL compute nodes retrieve the ONNX model bytes and load them into an in-process ONNX Runtime environment running alongside the SQL engine. 4) Data from the source table is fetched into memory as vectorized columns. 5) These columns are mapped directly to the ONNX model's input tensors. 6) The ONNX Runtime executes inference and returns output tensors, which are joined with the query stream. This avoids sending data to external ML endpoints, ensuring low-latency scoring.",
