    "answer": "The Fabric Data Warehouse uses Delta Lake under the hood. 1) Writes to the Warehouse generate Delta transaction log files (`_delta_log/`). 2) The Warehouse tracks operations in system views like `sys.pdw_loader_backup_runs`. 3) Point-in-time recovery (PITR) leverages Delta Lake's 'Time Travel' capability. 4) The Warehouse engine keeps transaction logs for a defined retention period (default 30 days). 5) When you execute a PITR restore, the engine restores the table schemas and points the system catalog to a specific historical transaction ID or timestamp in the Delta log, without restoring backup files.",
