    "niche": "Synapse Data Warehousing, SQL Analytics Endpoints, and Distributed Compute",
    "question": "Explain why queries hitting a Fabric Data Warehouse might fail with an \"Out of memory\" error even when the overall capacity utilization (CU) of the Fabric F-sku is below 20%.",
    "answer": "This happens due to query memory-grant limits. 1) Fabric capacities have a maximum memory allocation per user query based on the active F-Sku size (e.g., F2 has a very small memory limit). 2) A query doing complex hash joins or sorting on large datasets might exceed this query memory grant, causing the query to fail with OOM. 3) This failure is independent of overall capacity utilization: even if the capacity is 80% idle, an individual query cannot exceed its allocated memory slice to protect system stability. To fix, partition the query or scale the capacity.",
