    "question": "What is the impact of explicit T-SQL transactions (BEGIN TRAN...COMMIT) on the performance of a Fabric Data Warehouse compared to traditional SMP SQL Server environments?",
    "answer": "In traditional SMP SQL Server, explicit transactions hold locks in the transaction log (`ldf`), which can cause blocking. In Fabric: 1) Explicit transactions are translated into commits in the underlying Delta log. 2) Since Delta Lake is append-only, readers do not block writers. 3) However, long-running explicit transactions increase commit latency: the engine holds temporary metadata locks in the Warehouse control plane, which can delay metadata synchronization. Keep transactions short to minimize synchronization overhead.",
    "difficulty": "MEDIUM"
