    "answer": "Traditional SQL indexes (like clustered columnstore or B-Trees) do not exist in Fabric Warehouse. Instead: 1) Optimize data sorting: sort data on frequently queried columns during load using `ORDER BY` or `Z-ORDER BY`. 2) This groups similar values into the same Parquet files, allowing Delta's min/max file-skipping metadata to prune files. 3) Split high-cardinality keys. 4) Ensure stats are generated on columns used in filters. 5) Use partition columns effectively in queries to limit the physical file scan range.",
