    "answer": "Collation conflicts occur when columns in different databases have different collation settings (e.g., Case-Sensitive vs Case-Insensitive). To resolve this: 1) Explicitly cast collation in the query join or comparison using the `COLLATE` clause: `SELECT * FROM Warehouse.dbo.TableA A JOIN MirroredDB.dbo.TableB B ON A.Key COLLATE Latin1_General_100_CI_AS_KS_WS = B.Key COLLATE Latin1_General_100_CI_AS_KS_WS`. 2) Align database collations during setup if possible, or use views in the Warehouse that cast the mirrored columns to a standard collation.",
