    "question": "How does the Fabric Warehouse engine handle automatic statistics creation? Under what exact scenarios will the automated engine fail to generate precise histograms, requiring manual intervention?",
    "answer": "The Fabric SQL engine generates statistics automatically during query compilation. However, automatic generation can fail or be inaccurate when: 1) The table is small during compilation but grows rapidly (stale stats). 2) The query involves complex joins with expressions (e.g., `ON A.Id + 1 = B.Id`). 3) The filter criteria use table-valued functions or non-deterministic variables. 4) High concurrency limits background stats compilation. Under these scenarios, the optimizer chooses suboptimal join strategies. To resolve, manually create or update statistics: `CREATE STATISTICS StatName ON TableName(ColumnName) WITH FULLSCAN`.",
