    "question": "How does Incremental Refresh policy with Real-Time Data (Hybrid partition) optimize refresh times in Power BI?",
    "answer": "Incremental Refresh divides the dataset into historical partitions and a refresh partition. When a refresh occurs, Power BI only refreshes the data in the latest partition (e.g., current day or month), leaving historical partitions untouched. If 'Detect data changes' is enabled, Power BI queries a custom column (like a last update timestamp) to check if the partition needs refreshing. Enabling 'Real-Time Data' adds a dynamic DirectQuery partition for data newer than the refresh window, ensuring instant updates without executing heavy scheduled refreshes.",
