    "question": "How does the VertiPaq engine manage memory allocation during multi-threaded DAX query execution?",
    "answer": "When a DAX query executes, the VertiPaq engine divides the query into threads. Each thread scans a column segment (stored in compressed column dictionaries in memory). VertiPaq allocates temporary memory structures (hash tables and bitmap indexes) in the workspace memory allocation pool. If a query requires joining large tables, VertiPaq compiles a physical plan that executes joins in parallel. If memory limits are exceeded, the query fails with a memory limit exceeded error, rather than paging to disk, to protect the stability of the capacity.",
