    "answer": "1. Custom Parameterization file: Create a custom parameterization configuration file named `arm-template-parameters-definition.json` in the root of your ADF repository.\n\n2. Defining properties: Inside this file, specify rules to expose the target properties. For example, to expose the connection string and base URL of HTTP linked services:\n`\"Microsoft.DataFactory/factories/linkedservices\": { \"properties\": { \"typeProperties\": { \"baseUrl\": \"=-\", \"connectionString\": \"=-\" } } }`.\n\n3. Code Generation: During ARM template export, the ADF compiler parses this file and automatically adds these parameters to the ARM parameters file, allowing you to override them in your CI/CD release variables.",
