    "niche": "CI/CD, Enterprise Deployment, ARM Templates, & Git Integration",
    "question": "What happens to active pipeline triggers when you deploy an updated ARM template into a production Data Factory? How do you gracefully stop and restart triggers during deployment?",
    "answer": "1. Deployment Failure: If you attempt to redeploy or modify an active trigger using an ARM template, the deployment will fail because Azure Resource Manager cannot update resources that are locked in an active state.\n\n2. Graceful stop: Before executing the ARM deployment task in your release pipeline, run a pre-deployment PowerShell script to query and stop all active triggers in the target factory: `Stop-AzDataFactoryV2Trigger -ResourceGroupName $rg -DataFactoryName $df -Name $triggerName`.\n\n3. Post-Deployment: After the ARM deployment completes successfully, run a post-deployment script to restart the triggers: `Start-AzDataFactoryV2Trigger` to resume schedules, preventing deployment failures and ensuring consistent execution states.",
