    "question": "What is the performance and network latency difference between using an Auto-Resolve Integration Runtime and a Region-Specific Integration Runtime in ADF?",
    "answer": "An Auto-Resolve IR attempts to detect the region of the source/sink data stores and spins up compute resources in the closest available Azure region. However, this metadata lookup can introduce 50-200ms of startup latency. A Region-Specific IR (e.g., East US IR) runs compute strictly in that defined region. If your data stores are in the same region, using a region-specific IR eliminates the region detection phase, provides predictable network routing, and ensures compliance with regional data processing policies.",
