    "category": "ADF",
    "niche": "Security and Parameters",
    "question": "How do Global Parameters in ADF behave during CI/CD deployments across environments?",
    "answer": "Global Parameters are constant values accessible across all pipelines in a Data Factory. During CI/CD, the Git integration compiles your ADF resource definitions into an ARM template. By default, Global Parameters are exported in the `ARMTemplateForFactory.json` file. To change their values for different environments (e.g., setting a Dev API URL vs. a Prod API URL), you must enable the option 'Include global parameters in the ARM template' in the Git settings. This exposes the parameters in the ARM deployment parameter file, allowing release pipelines (like Azure DevOps) to override them during deployment.",
