    "answer": "1. Parallel DDL Contention: Creating temporary tables dynamically requires allocating pages. Multiple threads attempt to modify allocation maps simultaneously.\n\n2. Allocation maps role:\n- GAM/SGAM: Track extent allocation. Multiple threads compete to acquire locks on the single GAM page for the file.\n- PFS: Tracks page space fullness. Multiple threads compete to update PFS bytes.\n\n3. Contention: This creates PAGELATCH contention on these specific allocation pages. Mitigate by: (a) Configuring multiple TempDB data files (matching CPU count). (b) Enabling trace flag 1118 (forces uniform extent allocations) and 1117, which are native defaults in SQL Server 2016+.",
