    "answer": "1. B-Tree structure: A standard clustered index B-Tree leaf layer contains every single row of the table. Leaf pages are linked in a double-linked list.\n\n2. Filtered Clustered Index: A clustered index cannot be filtered; filters only apply to non-clustered indexes. A filtered non-clustered index B-Tree only contains rows that match the filter predicate (e.g., `WHERE status = 'Active'`). The leaf layer is smaller, reducing index depth and dictionary size, which speeds up index scans for matching rows.",
