    "answer": "1. Null Bitmap: Every record header contains a Null Bitmap section. It tracks whether columns are null.\n\n2. Fixed-length columns: Still consume their full defined byte size on the page even if null. The null bitmap simply sets the column bit to 1 (null), but the physical bytes remain on the page.\n\n3. Variable-length columns: Consume zero bytes. The offset array in the record header maps the column length to 0, and the null bitmap bit is set, saving storage space.",
