    "answer": "1. Large Pages: By default, Windows allocates memory in 4KB pages. Enabling trace flag `-T834` forces SQL Server to allocate the buffer pool using 2MB (or large) memory pages.\n\n2. OS Page Tables: Reduces the size of the OS Translation Lookaside Buffer (TLB), speeding up memory translation. However, buffer pool startup takes longer because SQL Server must pre-allocate contiguous physical RAM from the OS, which fails if memory is fragmented.",
