    "question": "Describe how SQL Server manages Extents when multiple files exist within a single filegroup. Explain the Proportional Fill algorithm and its failure points.",
    "answer": "1. Proportional Fill: When writing data, SQL Server distributes writes across all files in the filegroup. It allocates extents based on the remaining free space ratio of each file (e.g., a file with 10GB free gets twice as many writes as one with 5GB free).\n\n2. Failure: If one file grows out of space or is set to a fixed size while others autogrow, the algorithm fails, routing all writes to the autogrowing file, causing I/O hotspots and degrading storage performance.",
