    "answer": "1. Synchronous (Default): When a query compiles and statistics are stale, compilation halts while SQL Server updates the statistics, ensuring an accurate plan but delaying query compilation.\n\n2. Asynchronous: The optimizer compiles using stale stats but spawns a background thread to update the statistics, preventing compilation delays.\n\n3. Triggers: Statistics become stale when modifications (`rowmodctr`) exceed a threshold (e.g., 20% of rows plus 500). In modern versions, the threshold is dynamic (e.g., square root of table rows), reducing stale stats issues on large tables.",
