    "answer": "1. Buffer Pool: The memory space used to cache data and index pages in RAM.\n\n2. Clock Hand Algorithm: The Lazy Writer thread scans the buffer pool pages using a clock hand sweep. Each page header has a reference count (0-250). Each sweep decrements the count. If a query accesses the page, the count increases. If the clock hand encounters a page with a count of 0 during memory pressure, the page is evicted, ensuring frequently accessed pages remain in memory.",
