    "answer": "1. Hash Indexes: Optimized for point lookups. Consists of a bucket array. Each bucket holds a pointer to a row chain. (2) Bucket Count tuning: Must set bucket count to 1x-2x the number of unique index keys. If set too low, hash collisions occur (multiple keys in one bucket), forcing long chains and slow scans.\n\n3. Non-Clustered Indexes (Bw-Trees): Optimized for range scans. Uses a latch-free Bw-Tree that updates nodes by appending delta pages, linking node page offsets via a mapping table updated using CAS instructions.",
