    "answer": "1. Indexing Structure: Parquet divides files into Row Groups (containing Column Chunks), with metadata in the file footer. ORC divides files into Stripes, placing stripe-level indexes (like Bloom filters and row indexes) within the stripe header and footer.\n\n2. Nested Maps processing: Parquet flattens nested structures using definition/repetition levels (Dremel record assembly). ORC uses a type tree structure. Trino leverages ORC's index positioning to skip entire stripes, making it faster for nested map evaluations. Spark's vectorized Parquet reader performs better when reading flattened columns but suffers memory overhead when parsing deep maps due to record assembly latency.",
