    "answer": "1. Block Size Mismatch: If Parquet's row group size (e.g., 256MB) is misaligned with the object store's multipart upload part-size (typically 8MB to 16MB), a query reading a single row group must make multiple separate HTTP GET requests.\n\n2. Latency impact: This misalignment causes request fragmentation. The query executor experiences high TCP handshake overhead and socket waits, causing I/O throttling and inflating the tail latency ($P_{99.9}$) of distributed scans under heavy parallel workloads.",
