    "answer": "1. Apache Iceberg: Uses a tree of Avro files. The table metadata points to a Manifest List (Avro), which points to multiple Manifest Files (Avro) tracking actual data file paths and statistics. When querying a 10M file table, Iceberg performs partition pruning by scanning the Manifest List first, avoiding reading the rest of the metadata, keeping query planning fast.\n\n2. Delta Lake: Uses an append-only JSON commit log. Every 10 commits, it compiles logs into a Parquet checkpoint file. To query, the engine reads the latest checkpoint and appends the subsequent JSON log changes. For 10M files, reading and processing thousands of JSON log entries dynamically can cause high query planning times, making Parquet checkpoints critical to maintain performance.",
