    "question": "What is the impact of envelope encryption with frequent key rotations on the data compression efficiency and cache hit ratios of a distributed data lake query engine?",
    "answer": "1. Encryption Impact: Encrypting columns inside Parquet files before compression breaks repeating data patterns, destroying Dictionary and RLE compression efficiency and multiplying storage footprint.\n\n2. Cache hit degradation: To prevent this, apply envelope encryption where Parquet files are written normally (with optimal compression) and the entire file is encrypted using a KMS-managed data key. Rotate keys in KMS; this does not require rewriting the file, keeping query cache hits high.",
