    "question": "Explain how the OffsetLog and CommitLog maintain exactly-once processing guarantees in Structured Streaming sinks.",
    "answer": "1. OffsetLog: Driver writes the start offsets of batch $N$ to the WAL before execution begins. (2) Execution: Spark processes the batch. (3) CommitLog: Once the sink confirms the batch write is committed, the driver writes a commit marker for batch $N$ to the CommitLog. (4) Recovery: If a failure occurs before commit, Spark re-runs batch $N$, checking the logs to prevent duplicate writes in idempotent sinks.",
