    "question": "How does Spark handle late-arriving data in an Append output mode versus an Update output mode at the physical execution layer?",
    "answer": "1. Append Mode: Rows are only outputted when they fall below the watermark (meaning they can never change again). Retains all states until watermark expiration, delaying output. (2) Update Mode: Outputs modified keys immediately on every micro-batch. State is updated, but only expired keys are pruned, reducing output latency for downstream consumers.",
