    "answer": "1. Physical Plan: The planner inserts a `SymmetricHashJoinExec` node. (2) Dual States: Spark maintains two separate state stores (one for Left, one for Right). (3) Lifecycle: When a row arrives, it is appended to its side's state. The engine queries the opposing side's state to match keys. Rows are retained in states until event-time watermarks expire, cleaning both stores concurrently.",
