    "answer": "1. Log Anatomy: Stored under `_delta_log/` as sequential JSON commit files (`000000.json`, `000001.json`). Contains table metadata, file add/remove actions, and transaction markers.\n\n2. ACID guarantees: Delta uses optimistic concurrency. When writing, it prepares changes, writes the JSON file, and registers the version in the catalog. On S3 (which lacks put-if-absent), Delta uses an external lock manager or DynamoDB log store to guarantee atomic, sequential commits, preventing write overrides.",
